description:
Prepare OpenTofu configuration for the planned Lambda-based image processing system.

## Context

Per `openspec/changes/add-image-processing/design.md`, a Lambda function will handle image resizing. This task creates the OpenTofu infrastructure definitions so Lambda can be deployed via IaC when ready.

**Note**: This creates the IaC definitions but does NOT deploy the Lambda. Actual Lambda code/deployment is separate work.

## Planned Lambda Configuration

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| Name | `gallformers-image-processor` |
| Runtime | Node.js 20.x |
| Architecture | ARM64 (cost efficient) |
| Region | us-east-1 |
| Memory | 512MB |
| Timeout | 60 seconds |
| Trigger | S3 event on `v2/originals/` prefix |

## Required Resources

### 1. Lambda Function
```hcl
resource "aws_lambda_function" "image_processor" {
  function_name = "gallformers-image-processor"
  role          = aws_iam_role.lambda_image_processor.arn
  handler       = "index.handler"
  runtime       = "nodejs20.x"
  architectures = ["arm64"]
  memory_size   = 512
  timeout       = 60

  # Placeholder - actual code deployment separate
  filename      = "placeholder.zip"

  environment {
    variables = {
      S3_BUCKET           = aws_s3_bucket.images.id
      S3_REGION           = "us-east-1"
      API_BASE_URL        = var.api_base_url
      LAMBDA_CALLBACK_KEY = var.lambda_callback_key
    }
  }
}
```

### 2. IAM Role for Lambda
```hcl
resource "aws_iam_role" "lambda_image_processor" {
  name = "gallformers-lambda-image-processor"

  assume_role_policy = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17"
    Statement = [{
      Action = "sts:AssumeRole"
      Effect = "Allow"
      Principal = { Service = "lambda.amazonaws.com" }
    }]
  })
}

resource "aws_iam_role_policy" "lambda_s3_access" {
  name = "S3ImageAccess"
  role = aws_iam_role.lambda_image_processor.id

  policy = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17"
    Statement = [
      {
        Effect   = "Allow"
        Action   = ["s3:GetObject"]
        Resource = ["${aws_s3_bucket.images.arn}/v2/originals/*"]
      },
      {
        Effect   = "Allow"
        Action   = ["s3:PutObject"]
        Resource = [
          "${aws_s3_bucket.images.arn}/v2/small/*",
          "${aws_s3_bucket.images.arn}/v2/medium/*",
          "${aws_s3_bucket.images.arn}/v2/large/*",
          "${aws_s3_bucket.images.arn}/v2/xlarge/*"
        ]
      }
    ]
  })
}

# CloudWatch Logs
resource "aws_iam_role_policy_attachment" "lambda_logs" {
  role       = aws_iam_role.lambda_image_processor.name
  policy_arn = "arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/service-role/AWSLambdaBasicExecutionRole"
}
```

### 3. S3 Trigger
```hcl
resource "aws_lambda_permission" "s3_invoke" {
  statement_id  = "AllowS3Invoke"
  action        = "lambda:InvokeFunction"
  function_name = aws_lambda_function.image_processor.function_name
  principal     = "s3.amazonaws.com"
  source_arn    = aws_s3_bucket.images.arn
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket_notification" "image_upload" {
  bucket = aws_s3_bucket.images.id

  lambda_function {
    lambda_function_arn = aws_lambda_function.image_processor.arn
    events              = ["s3:ObjectCreated:*"]
    filter_prefix       = "v2/originals/"
  }
}
```

### 4. S3 CORS (for presigned uploads)
```hcl
resource "aws_s3_bucket_cors_configuration" "images" {
  bucket = aws_s3_bucket.images.id

  cors_rule {
    allowed_origins = [
      "https://gallformers.org",
      "https://www.gallformers.org",
      "https://gallformers.fly.dev",
      "http://localhost:4000"
    ]
    allowed_methods = ["PUT"]
    allowed_headers = ["Content-Type", "Content-Length"]
    expose_headers  = ["ETag"]
    max_age_seconds = 3600
  }
}
```

## Notes

- Lambda code deployment is separate (likely via GitHub Actions or manual)
- Consider using Lambda layers for Sharp library
- LAMBDA_CALLBACK_KEY should be in secrets management, not in code

Create centralized CSS classes in app.css for all form elements so styling can be changed in one place.

## Existing Pattern

app.css already has .gf-checkbox and other .gf-* classes. Extend this pattern to cover ALL form-related styling.

## CSS Classes to Create/Verify

### Labels
```css
.gf-label {
  display: block;
  font-size: 1rem;        /* text-base */
  font-weight: 500;       /* font-medium */
  color: #374151;         /* text-gray-700 */
  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
}

.gf-label-sm {
  font-size: 0.875rem;    /* text-sm */
  font-weight: 500;
  color: #374151;
  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
}
```

### Modal Classes
```css
.gf-modal-backdrop {
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  z-index: 40;
}

.gf-modal {
  position: relative;
  background-color: white;
  border-radius: 0.5rem;
  box-shadow: 0 25px 50px -12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 42rem;
}

.gf-modal-header {
  padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
}

.gf-modal-body {
  padding: 1.5rem;
}

.gf-modal-footer {
  padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
  border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
  gap: 0.75rem;
}
```

### Chip Classes
```css
.gf-chip {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.25rem;
  padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
  background-color: #dbeafe;
  color: #1e40af;
  border-radius: 0.25rem;
  font-size: 0.875rem;
